Currently their is no priority given to local requests made via RService.request . 
For prioruty implementation we can do the following:-
we can have a concurrent queu where if any remote requests comes in will
first drop its key at the tail and wait for its turn. When its is done it shall 
remove itself from the queue. Whe a local request comes in we always add to the top.
IF the system can handle at least two requests  concurrently. then the local user will never feel like this service is also being used by remote 


We can bring a concept of service permit:- with permits you get a fixed memory, compute, maybe thread(?). Their are limited permits avialable For local and remote we can have separate permits. And allow the service layer to define. 
With permits we can define something called scope : LOCAL, REMOTE and assign pool of threads for their execution. But why are we bothered about threading. This whole priority can be doen at the applciation layer

PrioritizeLocal: 
We have to non concurrent queues - one for local requests(with fixed size - calle thread will be blocked if quue is full)
second if remtoe requests that are made on this node also enqued into a queue

See let's say application has a budget of 5 concurrent requests
for this service which is blocking (if it is not then their is 
no need for doing anything special - as their can be a global cap on number of active service requests from peers on this node). Then app will delegate RService.serve request to a an Exector with 5 threads. Now suppose their are 10 remote requests piled up and 3 local requests - you would like to prefer executing local request firs for this service. 

MaxRemoteRequest(100) on each request
MaxThreadToServe
MaxThread
PrioritizaLocalRequest

MyService(RService){
    Executor exec_remote = Executor(thread_count=3, max_wait_capacity = 5);

    Executor exec_local = Executor(thread_count=2, max_wait_capacity=5); 

    remote_serve(){
        add serve to remote executor - if it is not full 
        else fail immediately 
        return
    }

    local_request(){
        add reuqest to local exec if full fail immedidately
        return
    }
}


